I assume that there will be only one <code data-v-8c9498c0>&lt;script&gt;</code> tag. If one is found, then the contents of the <code data-v-8c9498c0>&lt;script&gt;</code> tag is compiled down to ES6 + CommonJS using <a href="https://esbuild.github.io/" data-v-8c9498c0>esbuild</a>. This compiled JavaScript is then returned over the wire.</p></li><li data-v-8c9498c0><p data-v-8c9498c0><strong data-v-8c9498c0>In the Nuxt app,</strong> if a component module is included in the response, Nuxt will compile that code as part of the Vue component, on-the-fly, at runtime.</p></li></ul><p data-v-8c9498c0>This results in the following markup:</p><p data-v-8c9498c0><img src="https://static.dt.in.th/uploads/2020/12/11/journal-script-ssr.png" alt="" data-v-8c9498c0></p><p data-v-8c9498c0>For full changes, see the <a href="https://github.com/dtinth/notes.dt.in.th/pull/1/files" data-v-8c9498c0>pull request</a>.</p></details><!--]-->`);
